 22  In a monoidal category, we can take the tensor product of objects, `X âŠ— Y` and of morphisms `f âŠ— g`.
 23  Tensor product does not need to be strictly associative on objects, but there is a
 24  specified associator, `Î±_ X Y Z : (X âŠ— Y) âŠ— Z â‰… X âŠ— (Y âŠ— Z)`. There is a tensor unit `ğŸ™_ C`,
 25  with specified left and right unitor isomorphisms `Î»_ X : ğŸ™_ C âŠ— X â‰… X` and `Ï_ X : X âŠ— ğŸ™_ C â‰… X`.
 26  These associators and unitors satisfy the pentagon and triangle equations.
